I just took a peek at the WR1 relay in my own bus.
There is indeed a fuse holder on the red wire, from
the relay connector to the starter solenoid.  It holds
a 30A spade-type fuse.  I've never had to replace that
fuse and the relay has been working perfectly for well
over 5 years.
